# 5. Our Frontend Dockerfile

This is the exact Dockerfile structure we used.

```dockerfile
FROM node:20-alpine AS build

WORKDIR /app

COPY package*.json .

RUN npm install

COPY .

RUN npm run build

FROM nginx:alpine

COPY --from=build /app/dist /usr/share/nginx/html

EXPOSE 80

CMD ["nginx","-g","daemon off;"]
```

---

Now understand every line.

---

## Line 1

```dockerfile
FROM node:20-alpine AS build
```

Meaning

Create first build stage.

Why Node?

React application needs Node.

Why Version 20?

Stable LTS.

Why Alpine?

Very small image.

Approx

Ubuntu Image

```text
80-120 MB
```

Alpine

```text
5-8 MB
```

Smaller

↓

Faster download

↓

Less vulnerabilities

↓

Less storage

---

## AS build

Creates stage name.

Later

```dockerfile
COPY --from=build
```

will use this stage.

---

## WORKDIR

```dockerfile
WORKDIR /app
```

Creates

```text
/app
```

Inside container.

Equivalent Linux command

```bash
mkdir /app

cd /app
```

---

## COPY package*.json

```dockerfile
COPY package*.json .
```

Copies only package.json.

Why?

Because

```dockerfile
RUN npm install
```

depends only on package.json.

Docker cache works better.

---

Bad approach

```dockerfile
COPY .

RUN npm install
```

Every code change

↓

npm install again

↓

Slow build

---

Good approach

```dockerfile
COPY package.json

RUN npm install

COPY .
```

Much faster.

---

## RUN npm install

Downloads

React

Dependencies

Node Modules

Everything.

---

## COPY .

Copies remaining application.

---

## RUN npm run build

React source

↓

Optimized HTML

↓

CSS

↓

JavaScript

↓

dist/

Production build.

---

Second Stage

```dockerfile
FROM nginx:alpine
```

Now

Node no longer required.

Only static files.

---

## COPY

```dockerfile
COPY --from=build /app/dist /usr/share/nginx/html
```

Copies

Only

Production build.

Not

node_modules

Not

Source Code.

Smaller image.

---

## EXPOSE

```dockerfile
EXPOSE 80
```

Container listens

Port

80

---

## CMD

Starts

Nginx.

---

